<TITLE> A bright day for Bangladesh in ITF U/14 tennis tournament </TITLE>
<TEXT>
 Dhaka, Jan 19 (bdnews24.com)  Three boys and one girl of Bangladesh Saturday advanced to the next round of the Mobil ITF U/14 Asian Championship 'Group-2' beating respective rivals in the opening round at National Tennis Complex in Ramna. They are Biplob Ram, Sajib Passi, Hasibul Haq and Sharda Sharmin Alam. Seeded player Ram outplayed Wangchuck Gyalpo of Bhutan 6-0, 6-0, Sajib defeated Wangchuk Tandin of Bhutan and Hasibul beat Hasan Hussein of Yemen 6-2, 6-1 in the boy's singles. Besides, Cambodian Long Chomnith, Nepalese Shah Gaurab, Sri Lankan Wijesuriya Madusha and Dissayake Sharmal, Malaysians Zaw Naung Sithu, Soe Thaw Zim and Kwah Ji Kent also moved into the second round in the boy's singles event. In the girls' singles, Sharda Sharmin Alam defeated Gurung Pawitra of Nepal 6-4, 6-3 to book her second round seat while her compatriot Anika Samin Anjum lost to Nepalese Lisanovitch Astesha by 6-4 and 7-5. Lham Rinzin, Taliah Grace and Yi Sophany also won their first round matches in the same event. 
